The fifth leaf contains two forms, like that on the third leaf, one sor Henry IV and his queen Joanna, the other originally worded for Margaret the queen os Henry VI and her son Edward, Prinee of Wales. The latter has been altered, the nai-ne Elizabeth being inserted, no doubt on some occasion when such a form was used sor the queen of Edward IV. The versicles at the end have perhaps been added at the same time.
